-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Arkema, Fortum, Barclays PLC 
-- 
-- Thu May 15, 2014 02:11AM EDT
-- None



May 15 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Arkema and Fortum, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Arkema SA <AKE.PA>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutral  * Fortum <FUM1V.HE>: SocGen starts with sell rating * Barclays PLC <BARC.L>: Jefferies cuts target price to 325p from 345p; rating buyFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes.* Arkema SA <AKE.PA>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutral  * Barclays PLC <BARC.L>: Jefferies cuts target price to 325p from 345p; rating buy * British Land <BLND.L>: Jefferies raises target price to 771p from 766p; rating hold  * Bunzl PLC <BNZL.L>: UBS raises target price to 1650p from 1390p; rating neutral * Coloplast A/S <COLOb.CO>: UBS raises target price to Dkk 480 from Dkk 400; rating Neutral * Fortum <FUM1V.HE>: SocGen starts with sell rating; target price 13.3 euros * K&S AG <SDFGn.DE>: Barclays raises target to 28 euros from 26 euros; rating equal weight  * Magnit <MGNTq.L>: HSBC adds to GEMS Super 15 portfolio; rating overweight  * Mondi PLC <MNDI.L>: Barclays cuts target price to 1140p from 1170p; rating equal weight  * Prime Car Management SA <PCMP.WA>: Jefferies starts with buy rating